Build fedora sdcard image for raspberrypi5:

Note: fedora cannot support rpi5 fan. So we need external fan.

see https://docs.fedoraproject.org/en-US/quick-docs/raspberry-pi/#_installing_fedora_on_a_raspberry_pi_for_linux_users

cd ~/Downloads
wget https://github.com/worproject/rpi5-uefi/releases/download/v0.3/RPi5_UEFI_Release_v0.3.zip
wget https://archives.fedoraproject.org/pub/fedora/linux/releases/43/Workstation/aarch64/images/Fedora-Workstation-Disk-43-1.6.aarch64.raw.xz

cd ~/build-raspberrypi5/fedora
Plugin sdcard to PC.
sudo ./mkuefiboot.sh
sudo mkfs.vfat /dev/sda1
sudo fdisk -l /dev/sda
sudo mount /dev/sda1 /mnt
sudo 7z x ~/Downloads/RPi5_UEFI_Release_v0.3.zip -o/mnt && sync && sudo umount /mnt
Eject sdcard from PC.

Plugin usb3 stick to PC.
cd ~/build-raspberrypi5/fedora
sudo ./mksdcardimg.sh
sudo mkfs.vfat /dev/sda1
sudo mkfs.ext4 /dev/sda2
sudo mkfs.ext4 /dev/sda3
sudo fdisk -l /dev/sda
xzcat ~/Downloads/Fedora-Workstation-Disk-43-1.6.aarch64.raw.xz | sudo dd status=progress bs=4096 of=/dev/sda skip=4352 seek=4352 conv=notrunc,fsync 
sudo mount /dev/sda1 /mnt
sudo vi /mnt/config.txt ( add 
usb_max_current_enable=1
)
sync; sudo umount /mnt;
Eject usb3 stick from PC.

Plugin sdcard and usb3 stick to rpi5. Plugin wifi usb dongle to rpi5. Power on rpi5.

Disable power saving and screen saver.
sudo btrfs filesystem resize max /
df .
uname -a
cat /etc/fedora-release
sudo systemctl start sshd.service
sudo systemctl enable sshd.service
rpm -qa | grep -i kernel
sudo dnf install kernel-devel-6.17.1-300.fc43.aarch64
rpm -qa | grep -i kernel
add: exclude=kernel* to /etc/dnf/dnf.conf
sudo dnf update
sudo grub2-editenv create
sudo grub2-mkconfig -o /boot/grub2/grub.cfg
sudo sudo grubby --set-default /boot/vmlinuz-6.17.1-300.fc43.aarch64
sudo grubby --default-kernel
sudo grubby --info DEFAULT
sudo grubby --info /boot/vmlinuz-6.17.1-300.fc43.aarch64
sudo ls -l /boot/loader/entries
sync
free
sudo reboot

sudo dnf install yt-dlp mpv rfkill speedtest-cli glmark2-es2-wayland
speedtest-cli --secure
glmark2-es2-wayland

aplay -l
pavucontrol  ( select card 0 as default )

firefox -> youtube.com -> search YmDNhi07_Ho

yt-dlp -f 'bestvideo[ext=mp4]+bestaudio[ext=mp4]' hyUhEjtlDLA -o avemaria.mp4
mpv avemaria.mp4

Plugin ASUS BT500 bluetooth usb dongle to rpi5.
sudo rfkill list
bluetoothctl -> scan on -> scan off -> exit

mainline kernel 6.17.1-300.fc43.aarch64 cannot support rpi5 fan, sound, wifi, ethernet and bluetooth.
